definitions.definition: The lord 's power or privilege of holding a court in a district , as in manor or lordship ; jurisdiction of causes , and the limits of that jurisdiction.
An exclusive privilege formerly claimed by millers of grinding all the corn used within the manor or township in which the mill stands.
